Leading Social Science School Celebrates Anniversary 
The Graduate School under the China Academy of Social Sciences (CASS)
in Beijing celebrated its 20th founding anniversary on Friday.
President Jiang Zemin penned a congratulatory inscription encouraging
the school to become a first-class education base dedicated to
fostering experts in the humanities and social sciences.
More than 2,000 people attended the ceremonies in the Great Hall of the
People, including CASS President Li Tieying, Peng Peiyun and Xu Jialu,
vice chairpersons of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress.
The graduate school was founded on August 25, 1978, when the nation
initiated educational reform. The institution has granted 893 doctorate
and 2,235 masters degrees.
